Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Account
    Account Class is an abstract class that holds certain information about a bank account, with this information the user is able to perform certain actions with the information that range from making a balance inquiry, transfer, deposit, withdrawal, or payment on that specific account
    BankStatement
    Bank Statement class is a class that creates and writes to file that will store a specified customers bank statment for all their respective account
    BankTester  
    Checking
    Checking Class is an child class that inherits information from the Account Class.
    Credit
    Credit Class is an child class that inherits information from the Account Class.
    Customer
    Customer class is a child class that inherits information from the Person Class, with this information the customer class keeps track of all the persons accounts (Checking, Savings, Credit), a pin number, and the users full name.
    Person
    Person class is an abstract class that holds certain information about a person, with this information the user is able to perform certain actions like adding an account to the persons scope, or viewing all the accounts they have
    RunBank
    The RunBank class consists of static methods that operate on or return objects pertaining to another class.
    Savings
    Savings Class is an child class that inherits information from the Account Class.
